      "writtenOn": "2020-09-18T16:22:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That\u0027s a good question.\n\nMy initial reaction is that I have no other need of the gitiles API, so it would be moderately simpler to have all of my interactions be with a single Gerrit client (and I need to be able to fetch the \"latest\" commit on a ref)- but I\u0027m not fully convinced. What are your thoughts?",
      "parentUuid": "bd19bbed_affa48b7",
      "revId": "8578a23c6883511110547c9875d888d39e9316da",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
